<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She first revealed her weight loss in May, revealing at the time that she shed the pounds thanks to 'pasta, homemade bread and lots of housework.'</p>

<p>And on Thursday, Australian radio presenter and media personality Kate Langbroek showed off her trim figure as she enjoyed a date night in Italy with her husband. </p>

<p>The 55-year-old, who is based in Bologna with her man Peter Allen Lewis and their four children, looked incredibly glamorous in a black jumpsuit which highlighted her slim frame. </p>

<p>Date night: On Thursday, Kate Langbroek cut a glamorous figure and showed off her weight loss in a jumpsuit as she enjoyed a date night with husband Peter Allen Lewis in Italy</p>

<p>Kate shared a picture of herself and Peter on Instagram, saying that they were going for an aperitivo, or drinks at happy hour.  </p>

<p>'Arriving for aperitivo... under the watchful blinds of our old apartment,' Kate captioned the post. </p>

<p>Kate looked glam in her off-the-shoulder jumpsuit, which featured flared legs. </p>

<p>Shedding the pounds: In May, Kate debuted her weight loss after coming out of 10-week quarantine, telling an Instagram follower at the time that it was down to 'pasta, homemade bread and lots of housework.' Pictured at the time</p>

<p>She teamed the look with a Gucci belt, designer sunglasses and a colourful scarf. </p>

<p>In May, Kate debuted her weight loss after coming out of 10-week quarantine, telling an Instagram follower at the time that it was down to 'pasta, homemade bread and lots of housework.'</p>

<p>After another fan commented that the 'bread-and-pasta diet' didn't work for them, Kate offered further details about her weight loss.</p>

<p>'I know this sounds weird, but Italian bread and pasta is different,' she said, adding that using local olive oil makes for a 'magical' and healthy combination. </p>

<p>'Italian bread and pasta, plus olive oil': The 55-year-old also revealed her 'magic' secret to losing weight after one of her Instagram followers asked if she had followed a specific diet</p>

<p>'Looking great': The mother-of-four said that constant housework was helping her keep physically active while in self-isolation. Pictured: Kate at the start of quarantine on April 9</p>

<p>Kate previously explained that moving to Italy with her husband, Peter Allen Lewis, and their four children in January 2019 had improved her overall health.</p>

<p>After just four months living in Europe, she managed to lose six kilograms without actively trying and while still enjoying food, dropping from 89.1kg to 83.8kg.</p>

<p>'I always found it very hard to lose weight, because quite frankly, I'm not as interested in losing weight as I am in eating food. It's as simple as that,' she said on radio show Hughesy &amp; Ed in May 2019. </p>

<p>La Dolce Vita! Kate previously explained that moving to Italy with her husband, Peter Allen Lewis, and their four children in January 2019 had improved her overall health</p>

<p>Hitting the scales: After just four months living in Europe, she managed to lose six kilograms without actively trying and while still enjoying food, dropping from 89.1kg to 83.8kg</p>

<p>At the time, Kate credited her weight loss to Italian olive oil, and said she was having an 'Eat, Pray, Love' moment as she settled into her new life overseas.</p>

<p>She continued: 'There's no point in moving to Italy if you're not going to enjoy one of the greatest things about that country, and that is the food.</p>

<p>'Everyone keeps asking me if I've lost weight, and the honest truth is I can't answer because I don't have any scales, but I have noticed that my leggings are looser.'</p>

<p>New life: She previously said she was having an 'Eat, Pray, Love' moment as she settled into her new life overseas</p>
